Internship Offer 
Page 1 
 
 
 
Marlakunta Kedhareswer Naidu 
kedhareswer.12110626@gmail.com 
 
Re: Offer of Internship by Diligence Vault (India) Private Limited. 
Kedhareswer, 
I am very pleased to confirm our offer to you of internship with Diligence Vault (India) Private 
Limited (the “Company”).  The terms of our offer and the benefits currently provided by the 
Company are as follows: 
1. Internship Duration.  Your internship will commence on 27 October 2025  and will 
continue for an initial fixed term of One (1) month, which can be extended as per agreement 
between the Parties. 
Continuation of this engagement beyond the initial One-month term is not guaranteed and is 
subject to: (a) A formal and satisfactory review of your performance; and (b) The mutual written 
agreement of both you and Company. 
2. Stipend. You will be entitled to a monthly stipend of INR 15,000/-, payable in 
accordance with the Company’s standard payroll schedule.  
3. Working Hours. Your normal hours of work will be 8 hours, excluding 1 hour of 
lunch/dinner break, Monday to Friday. 
4. Leave Entitlement. Interns are eligible only for the following statutory and 
Company-mandated leaves: 
● Company’s Holiday Calendar 
● Mandatory Leaves (as required by local statute) 
● Sick Leave according to the Company’s policy for Interns 
All other forms of paid or unpaid leave, benefits, or entitlements reserved for permanent 
employees are not applicable during the term of this internship.

5. Status and Non-Applicability of Employment Provisions (Legal Status). It is explicitly 
understood that this engagement is an internship, and does not constitute a contract of 
employment. 
(a) Probation: A probationary period is applicable exclusively to permanent employees of the 
Company and shall not apply to this internship engagement. 
(b) PILON (Pay in Lieu of Notice): The provisions of Pay in Lieu of Notice (PILON) upon 
termination is reserved for employees and is not applicable to this internship. 
6.  Background Check and Reference checks. This offer is contingent upon a 
satisfactory verification of (i) background check, which includes but is not limited to criminal, 
education and/or background and (ii) reference checks.  This offer can be rescinded based upon 
data received in the verification. Company may reassess such information at any time during 
internship. In addition, you may be required to submit various documents as detailed in Annexure 
A for our records, during this process or on your joining date. 
7. Protection of Confidential and Proprietary Information.  As an Intern of the 
Company, you will have access to certain confidential information of the Company and you may, 
during the course of your internship, develop certain information or inventions that will be the 
property of the Company.  To protect the Company’s interests, as a condition of internship, you 
must sign and abide by the Company’s standard “Confidential Information and Invention 
Assignment Agreement”, which will be an attachment to the internship agreement that will be 
shared with you.  
8. No Breach of Obligations to Prior Employers.  We wish to impress upon you that we 
do not want you to, and we hereby direct you not to, bring with you any confidential or 
proprietary material of any former employer or violate any other obligations you may have to any 
former employer.  You represent that your signing of this offer letter, agreement(s) concerning 
stock options granted to you, if any, under the Plan and the Company’s Confidential Information 
and Invention Assignment Agreement and your commencement of internship with the Company 
will not violate any agreement currently in place between yourself and current or past employers. 
9. Non-Competition. According to the scope of specific jurisdiction laws regarding 
non-competition after termination of internship, you understand that the Company’s interests in 
protecting its investments, goodwill, proprietary information, trade secrets, and/or technologies,  
make it reasonable for the Company, to ask you to agree that you will not compete with the 
Company as stated in the Confidentiality Invention and Information Assignment Agreement.  
10. No Conflicting Activities; Other Employment. You acknowledge that you are 
required to devote your time, attention and abilities during working hours defined in the 
Agreement to your duties and to the best interest of the Company and may not undertake any 
other work during this time. During the period of your internship, you will at all times devote your 
best efforts and abilities to the interests of the Company, and will not, without the prior written 
consent of the Company, engage in, or encourage or assist others to engage in, any other 
employment or activity that: (i) conflicts with Company’s business interests, (ii) occupies your 
attention so as to interfere with the proper and efficient performance of your duties at the 
Company, (iii) is competitive with the business of the Company, or which could be considered to 
DiligenceVault 
Docusign Envelope ID: 4CD4891C-53BB-4ED3-B296-15EB27DE298A

nce of your duties at the 
Company, (iii) is competitive with the business of the Company, or which could be considered to

Internship Offer 
Page 3 
 
 
impair your ability to act at all times in the best interests of the Company (ii) would divert from 
the Company any business opportunity in which the Company can reasonably be expected to have 
an interest; (iii) could cause a disruption of Company’s operations or prospects or (iv) interferes 
with the independent exercise of your judgement in Company’s best interests.  
11. Termination and Notice Period. Either Company or you may terminate this 
Internship Offer at any point during the duration by providing the other party with a minimum of 
two (2) weeks written notice. 
12. Non-disparagement. You agree not to disparage the Company, its respective 
officers, directors, employees, stockholders, agents and affiliates, directly or indirectly, either 
verbally or in writing or otherwise, including but not limited to making negative statements, 
comments, or references about the Company’ services, facilities, operations, or businesses 
practices in any manner likely to be harmful to them or their business, business reputation or 
personal reputation, unless requested by subpoena, court order or applicable law. 
13. Tax Matters.  All forms of compensation referred to in this agreement are subject to 
reduction to reflect applicable withholding and payroll taxes and other deductions required by 
law.   
14. Governing Law. This offer shall be construed in accordance with the laws of India 
and shall be subject to the exclusive jurisdiction of the Maharashtra Courts. 
15. Internship Agreement. Upon completion of the formalities contained in this Offer 
Letter, you will be required to execute an Internship agreement (which will have as attachment  
the Confidential Information and Invention Assignment Agreement), which contains the detailed 
terms and conditions in relation to your internship including important representations and 
company policies that are to be undertaken by you prior to confirming you as an Intern with the 
Company. 
16. Entire Agreement.  This offer, the internship agreement and the Confidential 
Information and Invention Assignment Agreement (“Internship Documents”), once accepted, 
constitutes the entire agreement between you and the Company with respect to the subject 
matter hereof and supersedes all prior offers, negotiations and agreements, if any, whether 
written or oral, relating to such subject matter.  You acknowledge that neither the Company nor its 
agents have made any promise, representation or warranty whatsoever, either express or implied, 
written or oral, which will not be part of the Internship Documents for the purpose of inducing 
you to execute an agreement. 
17. Acceptance.  This offer will remain open until October 19, 2025.  If you decide to 
accept our offer, and I hope you will, please sign the enclosed copy of this letter in the space 
indicated and return it to me.  Your signature will acknowledge that you have read and understood 
and agreed to the terms and conditions of this offer letter and the attached documents, if any.  
Should you have anything else that you wish to discuss, please do not hesitate to call me. 
 
 
DiligenceVault

1. This AGREEMENT (“Agreement”) is signed and dated as of                     (“Effective

2. JOB TITLE 
You will be employed as AI Engineering Intern and Your main duties are those that 
were outlined to You during recruitment and/or the commencement of Your Internship. 
The Company may from time to time require You to undertake additional or other duties 
as necessary to meet the needs of the business. 
3. TERM OF INTERNSHIP 
Your Internship is expected to commence on or after the Effective Date as agreed with 
the Company and will continue for an initial fixed term of One (1) month, which can be 
extended as per agreement between the Parties. 
4. BACKGROUND CHECKS 
Your Internship with the Company is conditional on a satisfactory verification of 
background checks and proof of right to work in India. The Company may reassess such 
information at any time during Internship. 
5. PLACE OF WORK 
Your place of Internship can be either an office space assigned by the Company 
according to Your location and/or your current home address, or such other place as the 
Company may reasonably require for the proper performance and exercise of Your 
duties. Company may enforce a minimum amount of days in the office. You will also may 
be required to undertake business travel as the Company requests in order for You to 
fulfil Your duties to the satisfaction of the Company. 
You are required to inform the Company immediately if You plan to change Your home 
address or work location.  The Company will assess the impact of the change in address 
to the Company and where applicable make arrangements with You. You confirm that by 
undertaking the duties of Your Internship at Your home address You are not in breach if 
any covenant or agreement.  
6. DUTIES

A. During the Internship You shall: 
I. unless prevented by illness or accident, You shall devote during Your working 
hours Your time, attention and abilities to carrying out Your duties; 
II. not work for anyone else during the Company’s assigned working hours; 
III. comply with all reasonable and lawful directions given to You by the Company; 
IV. comply with the Company’s training, rules, regulations and policies in place from 
time to time in force; 
V. report to the Company of any approach by any person or company or firm or 
other entity, made with a view to recruiting You to work in any capacity for or 
provide any advice or services to a competitor or intended competitor of the 
Company or any of its subsidiary or affiliated entities, as reasonably practicable 
after any such approach has been made; 
VI. comply with the enclosed Confidential Information and Invention Assignment 
Agreement and 
VII. comply with the Company’s Information Security Policy, Code of Conduct or any 
other policy that is made available to You from time to time; 
VIII. report any wrongdoing or proposed wrongdoing related to the Company 
immediately upon becoming aware of it;  
IX. notify the Company immediately or as soon as is reasonably practicable of any 
regulatory investigation carried out by any regulator or investigation conducted by 
the police, or any other prosecuting authority, in relation to any criminal offence or 
alleged criminal offence, whether occurring before or during Your Internship, 
where You are the perpetrator or alleged to be the perpetrator of such criminal 
offence or alleged criminal offence; 
X. consent to the Company monitoring use that You make of the Company’s 
electronic communications systems and equipment for the purpose of ensuring 
that the Company’s rules are being complied with and for legitimate business 
purposes. 
 
7. INTERN’S REPRESENTATIONS 
You represent and warrant to the Company that 
A. By entering into this Agreement or performing any of Your obligations under it, You will 
not be in breach of any court order or any express or implied terms of any contract or 
other obligation binding on You. 
B. You were the only person that participated during the recruitment process and that You 
had no help from others while performing test assessments. 
C. You warrant that You are entitled to work in India without any additional approvals and 
will notify the Company immediately if You cease to be so entitled at any time during 
Your Internship. 
D. You had reviewed this Agreement and understands the terms, purposes, and effects of 
this Agreement;

E. You have not been subjected to duress or undue influence of any kind to execute this 
Agreement, and this Agreement will not impose an undue hardship upon the Intern; 
F. You have executed this Agreement on Your own free will and without relying upon any 
statements made by the Company or any of its representatives, agents, or Employees 
that are not part of this Agreement or is in writing; 
G. The execution, delivery, and performance of this Agreement by the Intern does not and 
will not conflict with, breach, violate, or cause a default under any agreement, 
instrument, order, judgment, or decree to which the Intern is a party or by which the 
Intern is bound; 
H. You are not bound by any employment agreement not disclosed or non-competition 
Agreement with any person or entity; 
I. You will not execute any instrument or grant or transfer any rights, titles, or interests 
inconsistent with the terms and conditions of this Agreement; 
J. While providing services to the Company, You will not engage in or be involved in 
activities related that are considered illegal and/or are in violation of Indian laws. 
 
8. THIRD PARTY AGREEMENT 
Your Internship with the Company may, in some circumstances be subject to the 
approval of third parties (normally Company’s customers), and their specific background 
check and rules. 
9. TRAINING 
It is the condition of Your Internship that You participate in any training deemed 
necessary by the Company for You to reach the required levels of attainment standards. 
10. HOURS OF WORK 
Your normal hours of work will be 8 hours, excluding 1 hour of lunch/dinner break, 
Monday to Friday. 
11. REMUNERATION 
Your gross salary is described in Your offer letter, and is subject to the deduction of taxes 
and applicable compliances as the Company is required by law to deduct. 
Payment is made by credit directly into Your nominated bank account. 
The Company may deduct from the salary any other sums owed by You to the Company. 
12. ANNUAL LEAVES 
Interns are eligible only for the following statutory and Company-mandated leaves: 
4 
Docusign Envelope ID: 4CD4891C-53BB-4ED3-B296-15EB27DE298A

sums owed by You to the Company. 
12. ANNUAL LEAVES 
Interns are eligible only for the following statutory and Company-mandated leaves:

●       Company’s Holiday Calendar 
●       Mandatory Leaves (as required by local statute) 
●       Sick Leave according to the Company’s policy for Interns 
All other forms of paid or unpaid leave, benefits, or entitlements reserved for permanent 
employees are not applicable during the term of this Internship. Any leave mentioned above 
shall follow the Company’s policy and approval and will be subject to Your manager approval 
and business needs. 
Please refer to the most recently updated holiday calendar 
13. SECURITY AND USE OF EQUIPMENT 
You may be issued with Company property; such as tools for Your role, including but not 
limited to: laptop, mouse and keyboard, and so on in order to perform Your day to day 
duties. You should not use a personal laptop not authorized by the Company to perform 
Your duties. The equipment issued remains the property of the Company at all time and 
should be used only to perform Your duties. It should not be used for unauthorized work. 
You are to take all reasonable steps to ensure the security and safety of the Company 
equipment; failure to comply with this request or the Company’s Information Security 
policy may lead to disciplinary action and/or termination. You will be required to 
reimburse the Company for any loss or damage to the equipment which is as a result 
from Your negligent act. 
On termination of Your Internship or at the Company request at any time during Your 
Internship the items must be returned immediately. Payment of the termination amount is 
conditioned on Company receiving all issued equipment. 
You undertake at all times to comply with all conditions of use which may from time to 
time be imposed by the Company on its policies with regard to the use of equipment, 
networks and systems provided. 
14. DISCIPLINARY RULES 
The disciplinary rules and procedures are set out in the Company’s Code of Conduct 
and/or other available policies. 
15. NOTICE OF TERMINATION AND PAYMENT IN LIEU OF NOTICE 
Either Company or You may terminate this Internship Agreement at any point during the 
duration of the Internship by providing the other party with a minimum of two (2) weeks 
written notice.

ement at any point during the 
duration of the Internship by providing the other party with a minimum of two (2) weeks 
written notice.

It is explicitly understood that this engagement is an Internship, and does not constitute 
a contract of employment. 
(a)   Probation: A probationary period is applicable exclusively to permanent employees 
of the Company and shall not apply to this Internship engagement. 
(b)   PILON (Pay in Lieu of Notice): The provisions of Pay in Lieu of Notice (PILON) upon 
termination are reserved for employees and are not applicable to this Internship. 
The Company reserves the right to terminate the Intern's Internship without prior notice 
or payment in lieu of notice if the Intern acts in contravention of this Agreement or if the 
Intern is guilty of any act of misconduct, as per the applicable policies of the Company. 
16. PERSONAL DATA PROTECTION  
16.1. For the purposes of the Personal Data Protection Bill, 2014 (India), by signing this 
Agreement, the Intern understands and gives consent to the collection, use, holding, 
processing, and disclosing of their personal data (as defined in the PDPA) by the Company 
including their data intermediaries, for all purposes relating to the performance of this 
Agreement including, but not limited to 
A. administering and maintaining personnel records; 
B. paying and reviewing salary and other remuneration and benefits; 
C. undertaking performance appraisals and reviews; 
D. maintaining sickness and other absence records; 
E. taking decisions about their fitness for work; 
F. providing references and information to future employers and, if necessary, to 
governmental bodies and agencies; 
G. providing information to the future buyers and potential future buyers of the Company, or 
the business(es) in which the Intern works; 
H. transferring their information to a country or territory outside India, 
I. providing and administering benefits; and 
J. monitoring of communications via the Company's systems.  
16.2. The Intern agrees and acknowledges that the Intern will need to comply with the 
Company's policies and procedures in relation to privacy and data protection as may be 
communicated to the Intern from time to time. The Company shall treat any breach of such 
policies and procedures as a breach of this Agreement. In accordance with the prevailing data 
protection laws in force on the date of this Agreement (or as amended from time to time 
thereafter), the Intern consents to the Company collecting, holding, recording, processing, 
using, disclosing, sharing and transferring to third parties and associate companies (whether 
within India or outside), personal data such as residence address, telephone number, 
photograph, educational qualification, details of relatives, all Internship-related and 
compensation-related information, government-issued identification and related information 
("Personal Data") and any sensitive personal data or information i.e., passwords, financial 
6 
Docusign Envelope ID: 4CD4891C-53BB-4ED3-B296-15EB27DE298A

ued identification and related information 
("Personal Data") and any sensitive personal data or information i.e., passwords, financial

Docusign Envelope ID: 4CD4891C-53BB-4ED3-B296-15EB27DE298A

 
information, sexual orientation, physical / mental health condition, medical records or biometric 
information ("SPDI"), relating to the Intern held either electronically or manually, and/or collected 
during the course of their Internship or at the time of appointment, for the purpose of the 
Company's administration and management of its Employees and Interns, its business and for 
compliance with applicable procedures, laws and regulations. Further, all Personal Data and 
SPDI collected/provided by the Intern at the time of appointment/during the course of the 
Internship with the Company will be handled by the Company's Internal policy that may be 
framed from time to time in this regard and applicable law. 
1. In the event of a change in the law applicable to data protection in India, the Intern 
expressly consent to the Company's continued use, storage, collection, and disclosure of 
their personal information and agrees to provide such additional consents and approvals 
in such form and manner, as may be requested by the Company. If the Intern chooses 
not to provide the Company with such additional consents and approvals, the Company 
may need to alter the terms of this Agreement. 
2. Further, the Intern agrees to inform the Company of any change in their Personal Data 
and/or SPDI within 7 (seven) working days. 
3. The execution of this Agreement by the Intern constitutes the Intern’s express consent to 
the Company for, among other things, holding, recording, processing, using, disclosing 
and/or sharing or transferring to affiliates of the Company and/or any third party, whether 
located in India or any other country, the Personal Data or SPDI for the purpose of 
compliance, risk management, operational purposes, administration, and management 
of the business of the Company, in compliance with applicable law. The Intern agrees 
that the Personal Data or SPDI may be shared, without the Intern's prior consent, with 
government agencies mandated under the law to obtain information for the purpose of 
verification of identity or for prevention, detection, investigation, including cyber 
incidents, prosecution, and punishment of offenses. The Company may also disclose the 
Intern's Personal Data or SPDI to any third party according to an order under the law in 
force, for instance, when responding to a summons or similar legal process, to protect 
against fraud and otherwise co-operate with law enforcement or regulatory authorities. 
4. The Intern agrees that when, during their Internship with the Company, the Intern 
processes personal data (whether relating to prospective, current, or future Employees 
of the Company at any time, clients or customers of the Company or any persons), the 
Intern will comply at all times with their obligation and the Company's obligations under 
relevant legislation. 
 
17. OBLIGATIONS ON TERMINATION 
a.     On termination of the Internship (however arising) You shall: 
I. immediately deliver to the Company all documents, books, materials, records, 
correspondence, papers and information (on whatever media and wherever located)

Company under Your possession or control; 
II. inform the Company of all passwords, pass codes, pin numbers and any other similar 
information used by Yourself in relation to any information technology systems, and/or 
any other secured property of the Company. 
III. per Company’s request, provide a signed statement that You have complied fully Your 
obligations under this section together with such reasonable evidence of compliance as 
the Company may request. 
 
18. DEDUCTIONS FROM SALARY 
The Company reserves the right to deduct any outstanding monies You owe to the 
Company from Your pay during and on termination of the Internship from Your final pay. 
This includes, but is not limited, to any previous error or overpayment, leave taken but 
not yet accrued, loans or advances made to You,  the cost of repair or replacement of 
damages or losses caused by Your misconduct, dishonesty, recklessness or negligence, 
instructions from the courts in relation to deduction from wages and the cost of any 
company property in Your possession which You fail to return within a specified 
timescale.  
19. VARIATION 
This Agreement cannot be amended or varied except in writing, signed by the parties. 
20. NO BRIBERY POLICY 
The Company has a strict anti-bribery and corruption policy. Any breaches of this policy 
may lead to disciplinary action, up to and including dismissal. 
21. FORCE MAJEURE 
In case of the occurrence of any event that is beyond the control of the Company, which 
cannot reasonably be foreseen and which substantially affects the performance of this 
Agreement or the business of the Company, such as natural calamities, pandemics, acts 
of Government, war, quarantines, terrorist attacks, a shortage of power or raw materials, 
accumulation of stocks, breakdown of machinery, etc., the Company shall have the right 
to terminate the Intern's Internship, if the Company, in good faith, believes that it is 
unable to utilize the Intern's services under this Agreement. 
The Company shall not be liable for any default or non-performance of obligations under 
this Agreement in case of any default or non-performance of obligations as a 
consequence of events of the nature discussed above. 
22. COLLECTIVE AGREEMENTS

Docusign Envelope ID: 4CD4891C-53BB-4ED3-B296-15EB27DE298A

of any default or non-performance of obligations as a 
consequence of events of the nature discussed above. 
22. COLLECTIVE AGREEMENTS 
8 
Docusign Envelope ID: 4CD4891C-53BB-4ED3-B296-15EB27DE298A

 
There are no collective agreements that govern or affect Your Internship. 
23. CONFIDENTIALITY 
You have an obligation of confidentiality that is further stated in the enclosed Confidential 
Information And Invention Assignment Agreement. 
24. SPECIFIC RESTRICTIONS AND COVENANTS 
In order to protect the Confidential Information of Diligence Vault (India) Private Limited 
and its business connections to which You have access as a result of the Appointment, 
You covenant with us that You shall not: 
(a) Secrecy of Diligence Vault (India) Private Limited and clients’ affairs.  
You will not, at any time during Your Internship or at any time after termination, for whatever 
reason, disclose to any person any Company information of a confidential nature relating to the 
Company or any clients of the Company. 
(b)   Company Opportunities; Other Employment; No Conflicting Activities: obligations are 
further described in the enclosed Confidential Information And Invention Assignment 
Agreement.  
(c) Non-Compete and Non-Solicitation obligations are further described in the enclosed 
Confidential Information And Invention Assignment Agreement. 
(d)  After the termination of Internship, for any reason whatsoever, the Intern shall not for any 
reason represent themselves as still connected with the Company or as still authorised to 
conduct business on behalf of the Company. Nothing in this contract shall prevent the Company 
and the Intern from coming to a mutual agreement in each case which protects each other’s 
interests and is specific to the circumstances of each case. 
Each of the clauses listed above are deemed to be independent and should any clause be 
judged to be unenforceable, then any such judgement will not make null and void or adversely 
affect the other clauses. 
It is agreed that these restrictions go only so far as is reasonable given the competitive nature of 
the industry and the market within which the Company trades, to protect the legitimate interests 
of the Company. The Company will not unreasonably withhold its consent and will not 
unreasonably seek to prevent any employee and Intern from earning a livelihood.  The Intern
